🚨BUILDING UPDATE 🚨 

So I’ve been sitting on my Buckhead building purchase because I’m preparing to do something with it that totally exceeds my comfort levels and I love it! 

I’m ANXIOUS , I’m UNCOMFORTABLE and I DON’T have all of the answers yet, buts that’s the fun part. 🤓

Ok back to the update— I enlisted the help of the amazing architects, Tate + Hansen and we are now past feasibility study and in the conceptual design. 

This building will be a mixed-use 6 story stick build with underground parking. (We’ll talk more on why I settled on this design later) 🏢

I don’t mind sharing my dreams before they happen because there’s nothing no one can do to interfere with what’s meant for you. I also do not elicit the advice from people who have nothing positive to contribute. 

I’ll continue to keep you guys updated (good and bad) to hopefully encourage at least one person to pursue your dreams relentlessly.

One necessary factor all entrepreneurs should consider is identifying your professional personality. Understand I’m not a psychologist or a medical doctor, but here’s what I know:

DEVIL’S ADVOCATE; RELENTLESS; PLANNER; PROCRASTINATOR 

You probably fall into one or more of these categories, but identifying your behavioral patterns will help you combat them. 

For instance, if you are or associate with people who are considered devil’s advocates, they|you will undoubtedly be discouraging and think of all the ways it won’t work. 

I personally identify with the RELENTLESS personality type. I don’t often get discouraged, I don’t need to tell myself I’m a winner bc I already know I am and I will map out whatever plan I need to, to achieve whatever desire I’m wanting. BUT bc I know I’m relentless I pay close attention to my psyche and my body for cues that I’m about to burn out before it actually happens.

I received an email one Monday morning about a request to schedule a chat about an upcoming tv show. I forwarded the email to my assistant to schedule a chat and didn’t think much of it after that.

A few days later I get on a call with show creator, Warren Robinson about being a judge on a new upcoming television series called Bury the Hatchet. He basically told me I had to do it. Haha. He said he saw me on my last television show and loved how I conducted myself. I replied “I can see that.” 😩🤣. 

Next thing you know, I found myself negotiating yet another talent agreement to be featured on yet another television series. I thought to myself how is this my life?!

Fast forward to this evening. I’m surrounded by the most talented, warm and supportive cast. This show is clever and funny and I can’t wait for you to see it. I also can’t wait for Season 2 bc if you’ve been following me, you know things only get better 🤪. 

Thank you Grey Media, Swirl Films, Peachtree TV, production and everyone else who made me apart of this project. 

Will you guys do me a favor and tune in? Thanks, guys 👩🏾‍⚖️

I did something Friday that challenged me all over again. It felt good. I was forced to put aside fear, anxiety, worry and doubt to speak to a room full of my  real estate attorney constituents. This was a speaking engagement I was not use to. Jokes are discouraged, written material must be substantive and the crowd was already well versed in the subject matter. AND I DID IT. 

My path to being a licensed attorney was not an easy one so to be asked to speak at The State Bar of Georgia’s Real Property Annual Convention was a full circle moment for me. I do not say this lightly when I say it was an honor. 

Now I’m excited to do it again and again until there’s no room for fear and the only path that exists leads to something bigger. 

What an experience. ✨
A lot to smile about 😃

Don’t play with me is the message.
